description: Retrieve historical information about a CIDR within an IPAM scope. For more information, see View the history of IP addresses in the Amazon VPC IPAM User Guide.

parameters.name: Cidr
parameters.description: The CIDR you want the history of. The CIDR can be an IPv4 or IPv6 IP address range. If you enter a /16 IPv4 CIDR, you will get records that match it exactly. You will not get records for any subnets within the /16 CIDR.

parameters.name: IpamScopeId
parameters.description: The ID of the IPAM scope that the CIDR is in.

nested_items.name: HistoryRecords
nested_items.description: A historical record for a CIDR within an IPAM scope. If the CIDR is associated with an EC2 instance, you will see an object in the response for the instance and one for the network interface.

nested_items.name: ResourceOwnerId
nested_items.description: The ID of the resource owner.

nested_items.name: ResourceRegion
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services Region of the resource.

nested_items.name: ResourceComplianceStatus
nested_items.description: The compliance status of a resource. For more information on compliance statuses, see Monitor CIDR usage by resource in the Amazon VPC IPAM User Guide.

nested_items.name: ResourceOverlapStatus
nested_items.description: The overlap status of an IPAM resource. The overlap status tells you if the CIDR for a resource overlaps with another CIDR in the scope. For more information on overlap statuses, see Monitor CIDR usage by resource in the Amazon VPC IPAM User Guide.

nested_items.name: VpcId
nested_items.description: The VPC ID of the resource.

nested_items.name: SampledStartTime
nested_items.description: Sampled start time of the resource-to-CIDR association within the IPAM scope. Changes are picked up in periodic snapshots, so the start time may have occurred before this specific time.

nested_items.name: SampledEndTime
nested_items.description: Sampled end time of the resource-to-CIDR association within the IPAM scope. Changes are picked up in periodic snapshots, so the end time may have occurred before this specific time.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The token to use to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.
